The paper focuses on developing a system for human-robot social interaction, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The system uses deep learning techniques such as neural attention and reinforcement learning, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The goal of the system is to exhibit socially acceptable behavior, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also mentions the use of multimodal data, which can be processed using machine learning techniques such as deep learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV).
